definitions.label_groups: colloquial , Scotland , Ireland , Geordie , Teesside , Liverpool

examples: There were, like , twenty of them.

definitions.definition: Used to precede an approximate quotation or paraphrase or an expression of something that happened.
examples: I was like , “Why did you do that?” and he's like , “I don't know.”
A customer walked in like , "I demand to see the manager!"

definitions.definition: a discourse marker used to highlight or put focus on new information or a new development in a story
examples: And then he, like , got all angry and left the room.
